README:
This visually-cued index finger tapping experiment
contains 18 younger and 24 older healthy right-handed
subjects. Subjects were either reacting to visual stimuli 
(visually-cued) or observing the stimuli without movement
(vision-only) in blocks of 1 minute each. The scientific
article (see Reference) contains all methodological details

- Nils Rosjat (September 11, 2020)
